<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,887,1344]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,410,887,912]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Diagnostic characters</emphasis>
. Elongately oval, high-spired shell; drop-shaped aperture; markedly prosocyrt external lip; thin parietal callus; slightly twisted columella; curved growth lines; fine, slightly wavy spiral striation. Protoconch: heterostrophic, blunt; 1 visibile whorl; diameter about 690 µm; surface smooth; transition to the teleoconch marked by a narrow prosocline furrow.
</paragraph>
