</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,887,1344]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,339,1103,1128]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Occurrence</emphasis>
. Box-corer samples BC04 (1 specimen), BC67 (1), BC72 (1); cores BC04 (2), BC05 (6), BC21 (3), BC51 (9), BC52 (1), BC72 (1). Maximum height: 
<quantity box="[763,852,1140,1165]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" unit="mm" value="6.5">6.5 mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,887,1344]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,503,1175,1200]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName box="[523,730,1175,1200]" class="Gastropoda" family="Acteonidae" genus="Crenilabium" kingdom="Animalia" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="exile">
<emphasis box="[523,730,1175,1200]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Crenilabium exile</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is distributed from the northern Atlantic southward to the Caribbean and the 
<collectingRegion box="[369,448,1212,1236]" country="Portugal" name="Acores" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Azores</collectingRegion>
and throughout the Mediterranean, at bathyal depths (
<bibRefCitation author="Jeffreys" box="[1075,1234,1212,1237]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refString="Jeffreys, J. G. (1870) Mediterranean Mollusca. The Annals and Magazine of Natural History, 4 (6), 65 - 86. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1080 / 00222937008696204" type="journal article" year="1870">Jeffreys 1870</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Nordsieck" box="[1248,1431,1212,1237]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refString="Nordsieck, F. (1972) Die europaischen Meeresschnecken (Opisthobranchia mit Pyramidellidae; Rissoacea) vom Eismeer bis Kapverden, Mittelmeer und Schwarzes Meer. Gustav Fischer Verlag, Stuttgart, XIII + 327 pp." type="book" year="1972">Nordsieck 1972</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Poppe" box="[151,377,1248,1272]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refString="Poppe, G. T. &amp; Goto, Y. (1991) European Seashells. Volume I. (Polyplacophora, Caudofoveata, Solenogastra, Gastropoda). Verlag Christa Hemmen, Wiesbaden, 352 pp." type="book" year="1991">
Poppe &amp; 
<collectingRegion box="[255,311,1248,1272]" country="Malta" name="Zebbug" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Goto</collectingRegion>
1991
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Di" box="[388,664,1247,1272]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refString="Di Geronimo, I., Rosso, A., La Perna, R. &amp; Sanfilippo, R. (2001) Deep-sea (250 - 1,550 m) Benthic Thanatocoenoses from Southern Thyrrenian Sea. In: Faranda, F. M., Guglielmo, L., Spezie, G. (Eds), Mediterranean Ecosystems - Structures and Processes, Springer, Milano, pp. 277 - 288. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1007 / 978 - 88 - 470 - 2105 - 1 _ 36" type="book chapter" year="2001">
Di Geronimo 
<emphasis box="[542,598,1247,1272]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">et al.</emphasis>
2001
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Galil" box="[674,797,1247,1272]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refString="Galil, B. S. (2004) The limit of the sea. The bathyal fauna of the Levantine Sea. Scientia Marina, 68 (supplement 3), 63 - 72. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.3989 / scimar. 2004.68 s 363" type="journal article" year="2004">Galil 2004</bibRefCitation>
). Among the bathyal faunas of Taranto, it was ascribed to the 
<emphasis box="[192,338,1284,1309]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Abra-Nucula</emphasis>
biocoenosis (
<bibRefCitation author="Di" box="[492,827,1284,1309]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" refString="Di Geronimo, I. &amp; Panetta, P. (1973) La Malacofauna Batiale del Golfo di Taranto. Conchiglie, 9 (5 - 6), 69 - 121." type="journal article" year="1973">Di Geronimo &amp; Panetta 1973</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1437,887,1344]" box="[199,854,1319,1344]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
